(SOBBING)

1106
01:55:40,265 --> 01:55:41,710
(DOOR OPENING)

1107
01:55:46,005 --> 01:55:47,711
Let's take a walk.

1108
01:56:19,706 --> 01:56:23,015
That's the deal, gentlemen.
He stays on this base

1109
01:56:23,076 --> 01:56:26,421
until we get
the final word from C-3
on how to dispose of him.

1110
01:56:27,479 --> 01:56:31,519
In the meantime,
if he does anything
but sit there in that chair,

1111
01:56:33,152 --> 01:56:36,599
we're gonna turn on
the juice and he'll be
incinerated immediately.

1112
01:56:36,655 --> 01:56:39,431
We've established
a 200-yard perimeter, sir.

1113
01:56:39,725 --> 01:56:41,899
If we deploy
the electromagnetic array,

1114
01:56:41,961 --> 01:56:43,997
there should be
no collateral damage.

1115
01:56:44,130 --> 01:56:45,164
MAN: Here they come!

1116
01:56:53,006 --> 01:56:55,280
I'm doin' this for you, Betty.

1117
01:56:55,440 --> 01:56:59,547
But one way or another,
we're gonna have to
prepare for the worst.

1118
01:57:04,016 --> 01:57:05,551
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1119
01:58:48,921 --> 01:58:50,957
I should have killed you.

1120
01:58:52,024 --> 01:58:54,265
And I should have killed you.

1121
01:58:55,728 --> 01:58:57,297
I wish you had.

1122
01:59:03,402 --> 01:59:05,244
I saw her last night.

1123
01:59:07,472 --> 01:59:08,974
Saw her face.

1124
01:59:10,342 --> 01:59:11,752
Brown hair.

1125
01:59:13,779 --> 01:59:15,189
Brown eyes.

1126
01:59:16,548 --> 01:59:18,220
She smiled at me.

1127
01:59:19,585 --> 01:59:21,529
She reached down
and kissed my cheek.

1128
01:59:24,457 --> 01:59:26,731
I can almost remember a smell.

1129
01:59:31,096 --> 01:59:33,235
It was like desert flowers.

1130
01:59:35,268 --> 01:59:37,110
Her favorite perfume.

1131
01:59:40,338 --> 01:59:44,217
It's my mother,
and I don't even
know her name.

1132
01:59:47,412 --> 01:59:48,686
(SOBBING)

1133
01:59:52,385 --> 01:59:56,162
It's all right, Son.
You go ahead and cry.

1134
02:00:03,296 --> 02:00:04,967
Go ahead and cry.

1135
02:00:09,100 --> 02:00:11,341
Cry. Crying will do you good.

1136
02:00:11,436 --> 02:00:13,006
Don't touch me!

1137
02:00:15,875 --> 02:00:18,149
Maybe once you were my father,

1138
02:00:19,412 --> 02:00:22,221
but you're not now
and you never will be.

1139
02:00:22,314 --> 02:00:23,885
Oh, is that so?

1140
02:00:25,618 --> 02:00:30,328
Well, I got news for you.
I didn't come here to see you.

1141
02:00:31,323 --> 02:00:33,895
I came here to see my son.

1142
02:00:35,261 --> 02:00:36,761
My real son.

1143
02:00:37,430 --> 02:00:39,341
The one inside of you.

1144
02:00:40,365 --> 02:00:44,143
You're nothing
but a superficial shell,

1145
02:00:44,337 --> 02:00:46,612
a husk of flimsy consciousness

1146
02:00:46,838 --> 02:00:49,876
ready to be torn off
at a moment's notice.

1147
02:00:50,076 --> 02:00:53,454
You can think what you like.
I don't care. Just go!

1148
02:00:59,484 --> 02:01:02,726
No, Son. Listen to me.
I found a cure.

1149
02:01:03,689 --> 02:01:04,895
For me.

1150
02:01:05,791 --> 02:01:08,203
My cells can transform, too,

1151
02:01:08,493 --> 02:01:10,974
absorb enormous
amounts of energy.

1152
02:01:11,329 --> 02:01:13,810
But, unlike you,
they're unstable.

1153
02:01:14,233 --> 02:01:17,542
Son, I need your strength.

1154
02:01:19,070 --> 02:01:21,175
I gave you life.

1155
02:01:21,606 --> 02:01:24,587
Now you must
give it back to me!

1156
02:01:25,578 --> 02:01:30,220
Only a million times
more radiant, more powerful!

1157
02:01:30,283 --> 02:01:33,627
Stop it.
Stop? Stop what?

1158
02:01:33,819 --> 02:01:35,854
Stop what?

1159
02:01:36,721 --> 02:01:40,692
Think about all those men
out there in their uniforms,

1160
02:01:41,460 --> 02:01:44,235
barking and swallowing orders,

1161
02:01:44,497 --> 02:01:47,876
inflicting their petty rule
over the entire globe!

1162
02:01:48,567 --> 02:01:51,104
Think of all the harm
they've done!

1163
02:01:51,737 --> 02:01:54,011
To you! To me!

1164
02:01:54,673 --> 02:01:56,118
To humanity!

1165
02:01:57,076 --> 02:01:59,851
And know this,
that we can make them

1166
02:01:59,912 --> 02:02:02,756
and their flags
and their anthems
and their governments

1167
02:02:02,814 --> 02:02:05,055
disappear in a flash!

1168
02:02:05,384 --> 02:02:07,021
You in me.

1169
02:02:07,386 --> 02:02:08,956
I'd rather die.

1170
02:02:10,689 --> 02:02:13,067
Oh, that's your answer?

1171
02:02:14,159 --> 02:02:18,506
Then indeed you shall die
and be reborn

1172
02:02:18,898 --> 02:02:22,345
a hero of the kind
that walked the earth

1173
02:02:22,667 --> 02:02:26,274
long before the pale
religions of civilization

1174
02:02:26,505 --> 02:02:29,109
infected humanity's soul!

1175
02:02:29,240 --> 02:02:31,220
Go!

1176
02:02:40,819 --> 02:02:42,094
(MOCKING)

1177
02:02:46,958 --> 02:02:48,664
Stop your bawling,

1178
02:02:49,595 --> 02:02:52,234
you weak little speck
of human trash.

1179
02:02:59,238 --> 02:03:02,014
All right. I'll go!

1180
02:03:03,743 --> 02:03:06,519
You just watch me go!
Hit it.

1181
02:03:07,179 --> 02:03:08,487
(SNARLING)

1182
02:03:17,823 --> 02:03:19,631
